President Muhammadu Buhari on Monday said efforts of the Katsina State Government in constructing and improving road networks across the state deserves commendation. Buhari commended the state government for its focus on linking economically viable areas in the hinterlands to markets, public institutions and schools. He said this while commissioning the 28 km Randa Doguru- Gallu Kwanar-Gwanti-Shargalle road in Daura, Katsina State. This was contained in a statement signed and forwarded to DAILY POST by his spokesperson, Garba Shehu. The President said, “investments in the infrastructure of the state will also encourage channelling of time and resources in positive economic and social activities and also enhance security.” He noted that Governor Aminu Bello Masari had shown commitment to the “development of infrastructure,” urging him to keep on investing for the future of the state. In his remarks, the governor said 18 roads across the state were earmarked for construction, and ten had been completed, while eight were at various stages. President Buhari had in August commissioned the Shinkafi-Yandaki-Gafiya—Abdallawa-Dankaba and Kwanar Sabke-Dan Aunai-Dutsi roads. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.